{
  "lessonId": "lesson-02",
  "generatedAt": "2026-04-06T16:21:56.362Z",
  "entries": {
    "turn-1-full": {
      "segments": [
        {
          "text": "English and Spanish are two related languages. English is considered a Germanic language, but roughly half of its vocabulary comes from Latin. We can convert this Latin vocabulary over to Spanish really easily, because Spanish is practically modern Latin.",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-1-full-1.mp3",
          "hash": "b34a9a8d29b61c3bb140b3c9c5511ccbd92972574a5beabcb21d0a70ba4b5304"
        }
      ]
    },
    "turn-2-full": {
      "segments": [
        {
          "text": "So we can identify Latin words in English and, with a few simple rules, convert them to Spanish. This gives us around 3,000 words.",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-2-full-1.mp3",
          "hash": "16e57d9794cdb510227dc56ab3ea97201ea564efb2e23aa4ea282936bbf3ca8a"
        }
      ]
    },
    "turn-3-full": {
      "segments": [
        {
          "text": "One of these rules is that words ending in A-L tend to work directly in Spanish. You just stress the final syllable. So for example, the English word normal — in Spanish, that's",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-3-full-1.mp3",
          "hash": "48692af952f1463b85d24ee9e2bb3d963b4745bf53b5071917a35081ef2ab65b"
        },
        {
          "text": "normal.",
          "lang": "es",
          "file": "turn-3-full-2.mp3",
          "hash": "d1d79c8f6abde907f94254ea2c09713ea8be329802813eb201456e44838967d4"
        }
      ]
    },
    "turn-4-full": {
      "segments": [
        {
          "text": "How would you say metal?",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-4-full-1.mp3",
          "hash": "4f86145502bea894cf196dab8178fc867fb6edcf63cdc8f0ba6ac5cd27a07309"
        }
      ]
    },
    "turn-6-full": {
      "segments": [
        {
          "text": "Metal.",
          "lang": "es",
          "file": "turn-6-full-1.mp3",
          "hash": "b45b1061b5c25cc97473d24aff26f3b11ed9c538e88e1795eb54d191a3d17919"
        },
        {
          "text": "Good. Spanish has five vowels, and each one always makes the same sound:",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-6-full-2.mp3",
          "hash": "ec90843f0ed38a63bf6e5c93ccc2bcc5fecb1c6cc7a3511f86a1af21e2d7df3d"
        },
        {
          "text": "A, E, I, O, U.",
          "lang": "es",
          "file": "turn-6-full-3.mp3",
          "hash": "6b4bd880b0bd61a316cc1ac162a6fd3af0f59f1ebbf6d9d59d252fad7b879de7"
        },
        {
          "text": "Keep them short and steady.",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-6-full-4.mp3",
          "hash": "ec4526a316f0f0b15b1d6895ee38e7a6bd1d7a9382525af629a687d32f0e39a5"
        }
      ]
    },
    "turn-7-full": {
      "segments": [
        {
          "text": "The word for 'is' in Spanish is",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-7-full-1.mp3",
          "hash": "7666535c8eacbad4a214d9ab64e678c7b9b9653a864ffde945b2979e069f64cd"
        },
        {
          "text": "es.",
          "lang": "es",
          "file": "turn-7-full-2.mp3",
          "hash": "73def5f1406151193a93fa64ac75a7d41afa35dc3c2ac42e48551595f9d591a0"
        },
        {
          "text": "E-S. And this also means 'it is', 'she is', 'he is', or even 'you are' when talking to somebody formally.",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-7-full-3.mp3",
          "hash": "a17c2b65b9b8ace9f7a48b8b36e60c19f483cf7521cddaa51711c3749c8c9f3c"
        }
      ]
    },
    "turn-8-full": {
      "segments": [
        {
          "text": "So now we can say 'he is normal' or 'she is normal'. How would you say that?",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-8-full-1.mp3",
          "hash": "79dede8a34541f247974c590a39be84f738a6761aea4d185add906241131859d"
        }
      ]
    },
    "turn-10-full": {
      "segments": [
        {
          "text": "Es normal.",
          "lang": "es",
          "file": "turn-10-full-1.mp3",
          "hash": "ac1eb3ecd3a34ab50771c2617bb2b5203c8a8f855e3d019d2767b01d80cce8d6"
        },
        {
          "text": "Good. One tip: in English, the S in 'is' is pronounced like a Z. In Spanish, always keep it as a clean S sound.",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-10-full-2.mp3",
          "hash": "2b764eed0f0358f674292d095c37efec9df8d47c3faa4faee6db30365fe8b2a6"
        }
      ]
    },
    "turn-11-full": {
      "segments": [
        {
          "text": "How would you say legal?",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-11-full-1.mp3",
          "hash": "cc2cc2458793b09a01afb9676c6d9b89dfb3675d1b8c2821a6d82b72fad883b5"
        }
      ]
    },
    "turn-13-full": {
      "segments": [
        {
          "text": "Legal.",
          "lang": "es",
          "file": "turn-13-full-1.mp3",
          "hash": "8869c6d1d48783ffbc1c7427de8024807cf96b209b3fbcece3646714c6cfdacc"
        },
        {
          "text": "Good.",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-13-full-2.mp3",
          "hash": "69b4cb7ec400c3cce7b9f1130780bd0e6d55ba3ff60b75455ccc93c20cf75eb6"
        }
      ]
    },
    "turn-14-full": {
      "segments": [
        {
          "text": "How would you say 'it is legal'?",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-14-full-1.mp3",
          "hash": "714624f1734eba991e5cb6b785327f666c77739af9068dcc69624c209bb7a289"
        }
      ]
    },
    "turn-16-full": {
      "segments": [
        {
          "text": "Es legal.",
          "lang": "es",
          "file": "turn-16-full-1.mp3",
          "hash": "43b0c8c7139e514045c476a3a9f3ecbcdf16e539c671906816b5308f9219b689"
        },
        {
          "text": "Good.",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-16-full-2.mp3",
          "hash": "69b4cb7ec400c3cce7b9f1130780bd0e6d55ba3ff60b75455ccc93c20cf75eb6"
        }
      ]
    },
    "turn-17-full": {
      "segments": [
        {
          "text": "How would you say illegal?",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-17-full-1.mp3",
          "hash": "06f66ba342ae828e3279432e43ed8c0267213e61ff657bc374d0126f0a39359e"
        }
      ]
    },
    "turn-19-full": {
      "segments": [
        {
          "text": "Ilegal.",
          "lang": "es",
          "file": "turn-19-full-1.mp3",
          "hash": "0d49b2306cf1fe5b2af9dfa1dd41f59de75de33f098f1baf2386090717199327"
        },
        {
          "text": "Good. In Spanish the I is like 'ink' and the E is like 'elephant'.",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-19-full-2.mp3",
          "hash": "3632a9ce051a11d51fdb2c4b2be341a278ddf56fec1719a8e9a0a4cb958a2036"
        },
        {
          "text": "Ilegal.",
          "lang": "es",
          "file": "turn-19-full-3.mp3",
          "hash": "0d49b2306cf1fe5b2af9dfa1dd41f59de75de33f098f1baf2386090717199327"
        }
      ]
    },
    "turn-20-full": {
      "segments": [
        {
          "text": "So how would you say 'it is illegal'?",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-20-full-1.mp3",
          "hash": "9fe8e74288bd5465a49aecadac4536e0c373c4b1598630ee0152f1611379f1a9"
        }
      ]
    },
    "turn-22-full": {
      "segments": [
        {
          "text": "Es ilegal.",
          "lang": "es",
          "file": "turn-22-full-1.mp3",
          "hash": "ec340224ac4c84eab3f6e0eb54929004f95e7d2b14611e24a0285d3300796d95"
        },
        {
          "text": "Good.",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-22-full-2.mp3",
          "hash": "69b4cb7ec400c3cce7b9f1130780bd0e6d55ba3ff60b75455ccc93c20cf75eb6"
        }
      ]
    },
    "turn-23-full": {
      "segments": [
        {
          "text": "What if you want to say 'he is liberal'? You do not need the word for 'he' if you know who you are talking about. You can just use",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-23-full-1.mp3",
          "hash": "88bc6544c69dfea7035610947dfdd3880f9f97e716f493a9bb9879e655003764"
        },
        {
          "text": "es.",
          "lang": "es",
          "file": "turn-23-full-2.mp3",
          "hash": "73def5f1406151193a93fa64ac75a7d41afa35dc3c2ac42e48551595f9d591a0"
        },
        {
          "text": "How would you say it?",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-23-full-3.mp3",
          "hash": "ab3c757e9fdf2759b57765297ba1702a2d1d7b605ffa1b8a907ad0c6a424273e"
        }
      ]
    },
    "turn-25-full": {
      "segments": [
        {
          "text": "Es liberal.",
          "lang": "es",
          "file": "turn-25-full-1.mp3",
          "hash": "930031e1acfec363eff7312b12629a871c5e6cd132c6f190c068e0bd0db149fd"
        },
        {
          "text": "Good.",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-25-full-2.mp3",
          "hash": "69b4cb7ec400c3cce7b9f1130780bd0e6d55ba3ff60b75455ccc93c20cf75eb6"
        }
      ]
    },
    "turn-26-full": {
      "segments": [
        {
          "text": "Now Spanish is much more phonetic than English. The letters represent the same sound. So with 'natural', you don't just want to change the accent and say it like English. You want to think how it's written and pronounce the letters as they are.",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-26-full-1.mp3",
          "hash": "4700f475b2f5d5fb9c74d2429ed2b1edb9439fe3cc274999702fbc07b63dc74d"
        }
      ]
    },
    "turn-27-full": {
      "segments": [
        {
          "text": "How do you think you would say natural in Spanish?",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-27-full-1.mp3",
          "hash": "3ed1db212ec27a49eacdb72ce952e2af8854296f3647da3e7ea3d2ead2386f39"
        }
      ]
    },
    "turn-29-full": {
      "segments": [
        {
          "text": "Natural.",
          "lang": "es",
          "file": "turn-29-full-1.mp3",
          "hash": "098384f1b05c60dd3e8d34df9ee96a99783805c1e4e0049830a9bee14bc0399e"
        },
        {
          "text": "Good. Remember to pronounce every letter as written - A sounds like ah, and U sounds like oo.",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-29-full-2.mp3",
          "hash": "5be054be88da5a6c82bc2863dd778edc42b5e264f3b95242aabd1c8239b451a4"
        },
        {
          "text": "Natural.",
          "lang": "es",
          "file": "turn-29-full-3.mp3",
          "hash": "098384f1b05c60dd3e8d34df9ee96a99783805c1e4e0049830a9bee14bc0399e"
        },
        {
          "text": "And stress the final syllable.",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-29-full-4.mp3",
          "hash": "16cef30381927910cc2d8d9fc66424637f60b36422072657556a8aa57b53ae55"
        }
      ]
    },
    "turn-30-full": {
      "segments": [
        {
          "text": "If you want to say 'it isn't' or 'it's not', the word for 'not' is",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-30-full-1.mp3",
          "hash": "93cf34ce2ec396bca0f5b05f86bcdc421a2f2889b3c336f2429470350db88087"
        },
        {
          "text": "no.",
          "lang": "es",
          "file": "turn-30-full-2.mp3",
          "hash": "7c301cdcc60f5a6039e532f7ddb03fecaa14305509e8240dc9f075d63a9d6434"
        },
        {
          "text": "You put",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-30-full-3.mp3",
          "hash": "8693e997d346f1c9201f90833d881db814b761d9f67ebd1d2a7300e96586835e"
        },
        {
          "text": "no",
          "lang": "es",
          "file": "turn-30-full-4.mp3",
          "hash": "e44058d78fedc84c827371a9d85127cff2fd79d4ea7766b292cbd10d12afaad3"
        },
        {
          "text": "before",
          "lang": "en",
          "file": "turn-30-full-5.mp3",
          "hash": "fd442ae8724755044be0553e69b723af1ecbc4829f6bf508043d27516a700f6f"
        },
        {
          "text": "es",
          "lang": "es",
